  {
    "caption": "Figure 1: Illustration of the neural architecture. Each HGRN layer consists of a token mixer HGRU and a channel mixer GLU. HGRU employs linear recurrence in the complex domain: ht = \u03bbt \u2299 exp(i\u03b8)\u2299 ht\u22121 + (1\u2212 \u03bbt)\u2299 ct. Here ct is the input vector, \u03b8 is the rotation angle, \u00b5t is the output of the original forget gate, \u03b3k is the lower bound of the kth layer, \u03bb is the resulting data dependent decay rate: \u03bbt = \u03b3k + (1\u2212 \u03b3k)\u2299 \u00b5t.",
